# Frontend Standards

## 1. Semantic HTML5

Use semantic elements instead of generic `<div>` wrappers for better accessibility and SEO.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div className="header">…</div>
<div className="main-content">…</div>
<div className="footer">…</div>

// ✅ GOOD
<header>…</header>
<main>…</main>
<footer>…</footer>
```

Prefer `<section>`, `<article>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<figure>`, `<figcaption>`, `<time>`, and `<address>` where they convey meaning. Only use `<div>` for purely presentational grouping.

## 2. 8px Grid Spacing

All spacing (margin, padding, gap) must be multiples of **8px** (0.5rem). Use Tailwind's corresponding values:

| Pixels | Tailwind | rem   |
|--------|----------|-------|
| 8      | `2`      | 0.5   |
| 16     | `4`      | 1     |
| 24     | `6`      | 1.5   |
| 32     | `8`      | 2     |
| 40     | `10`     | 2.5   |
| 48     | `12`     | 3     |

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — 20px is not on the 8px grid
<div className="p-5 gap-7">…</div>

// ✅ GOOD — 16px and 24px are on the grid
<div className="p-4 gap-6">…</div>
```

## 3. Reduced-Motion Accessibility

All animations must be disabled or toned down when the user prefers reduced motion.

**CSS / Tailwind:**
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

**Framer Motion (used in this project):**
```tsx
import { useReducedMotion } from "framer-motion";

function Component() {
  const prefersReduced = useReducedMotion();
  return (
    <motion.div
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: prefersReduced ? 0 : -12 }}
      transition={prefersReduced ? { duration: 0 } : { duration: 0.4 }}
    />
  );
}
```

## 4. CSS Variables for Colors

Define all colors as CSS custom properties (via Tailwind `@theme` or `:root`) so themes can be swapped by reassigning variables. Never use raw hex/rgb values inline or in class utilities.

```css
/* ✅ Define in index.css @theme block */
@theme {
  --color-primary: #2845D6;
  --color-surface: #0a0a1a;
  --color-text: #e2e8f0;
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded color
<div className="bg-[#0a0a1a] text-[#e2e8f0]">…</div>

// ✅ GOOD — uses theme variable
<div className="bg-surface text-text">…</div>
```
